          "merged_at": "2025-11-16T13:58:50Z"
        },
        "body": "## 🔐 JWT Authentication Added\r\n\r\n### ✅ Summary\r\nThis PR adds complete JWT-based authentication to the backend using Prisma + MongoDB.  \r\nIt introduces secure user registration, login, token generation, and protected routes.\r\n\r\n### 🚀 Features Added\r\n- New **JWT middleware** for verifying protected routes\r\n- **Register** API (`POST /auth/register`)\r\n- **Login** API (`POST /auth/login`)\r\n- Password hashing using **bcryptjs**\r\n- Token generation using **jsonwebtoken**\r\n- Prisma integration with the updated `User` model\r\n- Clean folder structure under `/backend/jwt`\r\n\r\n### 📁 New Files\r\n- `backend/jwt/auth.js`\r\n- `backend/jwt/register+login.js`\r\n\r\n### 🔒 Security\r\n- Uses environment-based `JWT_SECRET`\r\n- Ensures authorization via Bearer token in headers\r\n- Prevents duplicate accounts with unique email validation\r\n\r\n### 🧪 How to Test\r\n1. Run the backend server.\r\n2. Test in Postman:\r\n   - `POST /auth/register` — Register a new user\r\n   - `POST /auth/login` — Get JWT token\r\n   - Use the token in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` to access protected routes\r\n\r\n### 📌 Notes\r\n- Does not interfere with existing Google OAuth setup.\r\n- Fully compatible with Prisma + MongoDB connection.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n",
